<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HYDRO-MAX II BRAKE MONITOR SYSTEM - DESCRIPTION - BRAKE AND STOP LIGHT SWITCHES</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="6">
        <title>BRAKE AND STOP LIGHT SWITCHES</title>
        <para>Brake and stop light switches (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0826802">Figure 2</hotlnk>,
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0826803">Figure 3</hotlnk>,
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0826804">Figure 4</hotlnk>, and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0826805">Figure 5</hotlnk>) are utilized to control the vehicle's brake lights, cruise
            control where applicable, and Hydro-Max brake assembly on vehicles with hydraulic brakes.
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0826806">Figure 6</hotlnk>
            refers to a switch that is no longer used. These applications have been changed over to push button switch
            2037331C1. Most vehicles utilize two switches or a switch assembly containing twin contacts. The 3000RE bus
            utilizes a hall effect switch and magnet to operate the bus's brake lights and Hydro-Max brake assembly.
            Refer to the Switch Types Table,
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0826807">Figure 7</hotlnk>, for switch application information.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0826802" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg08/G0826802.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Dual Switch Assembly 2026921C1</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0826803" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg08/G0826803.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
            <caption>Hall Effect Switch 2042091C91</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0826804" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg08/G0826804.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
            <caption>Push Button Switch 2037331C1</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0826805" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg08/G0826805.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
            <caption>Single Switch Used as Pair 0358560C1</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0826806" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg08/G0826806.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Hydraulic Switch Retrofitted to Push Button Switch 2037331C1</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0826807" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg08/G0826807.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
            <caption>Switch Types - Model Vs. Build Date</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>A. DUAL SWITCH ASSEMBLY 2026921C1, SEE FIGURE 2</callout1>
                <callout1>B. HALL EFFECT SWITCH 2042091C91, SEE FIGURE 3</callout1>
                <callout1>C. PUSH BUTTON SWITCH 2037331C1, SEE FIGURE 4</callout1>
                <callout1>D. SINGLE SWITCH USED AS PAIR 0358560C1, SEE FIGURE 5</callout1>
                <callout1>E. HYDRAULIC SWITCH USED AS PAIR 1677210C91, RETROFITTED TO PUSH BUTTON SWITCH 2037331C1, SEE
                    FIGURE 6
                </callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
